IEEE 802.11be (WiFi 7) introduced operating class 137 for 320MHz
channels in the 6GHz band. Without this entry, iwd silently discards
6GHz BSS candidates advertised with oper class 137 in Reduced Neighbor
Reports, preventing WiFi 7 clients from connecting to 6GHz networks.

This patch adds:
1. Operating class 137 to the e4_operating_classes table with the
   correct 320MHz channel spacing and center frequency indices
   (31, 63, 95, 127, 159, 191) per IEEE 802.11be Table E-4.
2. Extends the oper_class_to_band_global range from [131...136] to
   [131...137] so the band lookup returns BAND_FREQ_6_GHZ for class 137.

Tested with Intel Wi-Fi 7 BE211 against UniFi U7 Pro Max AP.

Signed-off-by: Spencer Bull <spencer.bull@dell.com>

--- a/src/band.c
+++ b/src/band.c
@@ -899,7 +899,14 @@
 		.starting_frequency = 5925,
 		.channel_spacing = 20,
 		.center_frequencies = { 2 },
-	}
+	},
+	{
+		/* WiFi 7 (802.11be) 320 MHz channels in 6 GHz band */
+		.operating_class = 137,
+		.starting_frequency = 5950,
+		.channel_spacing = 320,
+		.center_frequencies = { 31, 63, 95, 127, 159, 191 },
+	},
 };

 static const struct operating_class_info *e4_find_opclass(uint32_t opclass)
@@ -1478,7 +1485,7 @@
 static const enum band_freq oper_class_to_band_global[] = {
 	[81 ... 84]   = BAND_FREQ_2_4_GHZ,
 	[104 ... 130] = BAND_FREQ_5_GHZ,
-	[131 ... 136] = BAND_FREQ_6_GHZ,
+	[131 ... 137] = BAND_FREQ_6_GHZ,
 };

 /* Annex E, table E-5 */
